What is an Abstract Syntax Tree?

div.style: font-family: Inter, sans-serif; font-size: 10px; color: #475569; line-height: 1.4;

foreignObject.div: An AST represents SQL as a tree structure, enabling programs to analyze, transform, validate, or rewrite queries programmatically.

g.text: Parser speed affects rule compilation. Faster parsing = faster subscription setup and rule updates.

div.div: Parsing overhead accumulates. A 2x slower parser means 2x more latency and CPU cost at scale.
A parser that fails on valid SQL breaks the pipeline. 100% compatibility is required for production.

g.text: *sql-parse only parses 30% of queries (complex PG syntax unsupported). Zero-copy reduces allocations.
992 queries from Gretel AI synthetic dataset
sql-parse achieves 98% compatibility on INSERT (simpler syntax), making comparison more meaningful.
983 queries from Gretel AI synthetic dataset
pg_parse is ~1.45x faster than pg_query.rs despite both using libpg_query—FFI bridge efficiency matters.
933 queries from Gretel AI synthetic dataset
DELETE is simplest. FFI overhead proportionally larger for simple statements—pure Rust shows biggest advantage.
